                  <handDesc>
                     
                     <handNote xml:id="h1" script="Ethiopic">
                        <seg type="script">Fine.</seg>
                        <seg type="ink">Black, red</seg>
                        <date>19th century (?)</date>
                        <list type="abbreviations">
                           <item>Throughout the text:</item>
                           <item>ይካ፡ for ይብል፡ ካህን፡</item>
                           <item>ይዲ፡ for ይብል፡ ዲያቆን፡</item>
                           <item>ይሕ፡ for ይብል፡ ሕዝብ፡</item>
                        </list>
                        <seg type="rubrication">Nomina sacra; the name of the Apostle Paul on fol.
                           18va; directives to the ministers and their abbreviations; initial words
                           or title of the prayers; the words wa-ʾǝmzǝ “and then”, ḥawarya “apostle”
                           on fol. 15va and gǝbra “act” on fol. 16rb; elements of the punctuation
                           signs; elements of Ethiopic numerals. 
 
 A few lines are
                           rubricated on the incipit page, alternating with black lines.</seg>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <list>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- A sign in the shape of cross (possibly tämälläs-sign, but no omitted text passages are indicated in the margin) on fols. 13r, 8v, 24r. - Omitted words inserted interlineally: e.g., fols. 6ra, 21ra-rb, 25ra. - Erasures marked with thin lines: e.g., fols. 18vb, 24va. - Corrections written over erasures: e.g., fols. 5rb, 16vb, 17ra, 19ra, 24ra-va.</item>
                     </list>
                  </additions>
